				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{c}P_T\left( {S_x,S_y,C} \right) = 1 - hygecdf\left( {X - 1,M,K,N} \right)\\ = 1 - \mathop {\sum}\limits_{f = 0}^X {\frac{{\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} K \\ f \end{array}} \right)\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {M - K} \\ {N - f} \end{array}} \right)}}{{\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} M \\ N \end{array}} \right)}}} \end{array}$$\end{document}PTSx,Sy,C=1−hygecdfX−1,M,K,N=1−∑f=0XKfM−KN−fMNWhere Sx and Sy are two SNPs; M is the total number of samples; N is the total number of samples in class C; K is the total number of samples that have genotype T; X is the total number of samples that have genotype T in class C.

